Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.80,0:17:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[school bells]
Dialogue: 0,00:17:52.133,00:17:55.486,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When pain says, “I'm here,”
Dialogue: 0,00:17:56.688,00:18:00.108,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I say, “So are they.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.25,0:18:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,00:18:03.854,00:18:04.277,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ALEVE
Dialogue: 0,00:18:04.758,00:18:05.898,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Who do you take it\Nfor?
Dialogue: 0,00:20:53.328,00:20:54.378,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Russ ]\NDad had it under control.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:54.498,00:20:58.578,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I mean, for 15 years,\Neverything was fine until--\N- Until what?
Dialogue: 0,00:20:59.088,00:21:01.638,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad left you a message.\NHe said, "Stop looking."\NYou didn't.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:02.547,00:21:03.617,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is my fault?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:03.888,00:21:05.598,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, consequences\Naren't the same as fault.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:07.248,00:21:09.288,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My parole officer\Nis very philosophical.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:09.438,00:21:13.308,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, all we have is\Na voice tape of Dad saying,\N"Back off,"
Dialogue: 0,00:21:13.398,00:21:17.118,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and a little silver dolphin\Nthat I found at Mom's grave.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:17.988,00:21:19.878,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's as far as\Nthe investigation has gone.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:20.028,00:21:22.488,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- According to Booth.\N- What? Booth and I\Nare partners.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:22.548,00:21:24.078,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tempe, he's F.B.I.\NYou aren't.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:24.498,00:21:28.097,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the daughter\Nof a career criminal and\Nthe sister of a loser on parole.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:28.638,00:21:28.998,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:30.948,00:21:33.137,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't let anyone else\Ncall you a loser, Russ.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:33.137,00:21:34.248,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What makes you think\Nyou're allowed?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:35.988,00:21:36.498,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I love you too.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:39.918,00:21:43.127,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What you're asking\Nis the kind of thing\Nthat destroys careers.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:43.368,00:21:45.978,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the time I was\Na little girl, I dreamed\Nof putting bad men in jail.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:46.006,00:21:49.787,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put that back. Which is why\NI became an Assistant\NUnited States Attorney.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:49.848,00:21:52.125,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to help me.\NOf course\NI have to help you!
Dialogue: 0,00:21:52.368,00:21:55.278,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Marvin Beckett is still a hero\Nto a lot of African Americans.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:55.308,00:21:57.618,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some of us never believed\Nhe killed this F.B.I. boy.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:57.828,00:22:01.038,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you buy me breakfast,\Ntell me you found a way\Nto clear his name,
Dialogue: 0,00:22:01.038,00:22:03.828,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,release him out\Nof wrongful incarceration\Nafter 30 years?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:04.038,00:22:06.048,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot walk away,\Nwhich you already know!
Dialogue: 0,00:22:06.288,00:22:08.328,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Maybe you should have\Nsome more coffee.\N- Of course I want more coffee.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:08.328,00:22:11.627,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We have to come up\Nwith our plan of attack.\N- I was thinking Judge Moran--
Dialogue: 0,00:22:11.627,00:22:15.078,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should exhume Gus Harper.\NSee if your genius\Nscientist partner...
Dialogue: 0,00:22:15.108,00:22:19.725,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can ascertain whether he died\Nin the manner the F.B.I.\Nsaid he died 30 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:19.758,00:22:21.524,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Moran's got a long--\N- No. We want Kemper.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:21.554,00:22:25.727,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- "Hang 'em High" Kemper?\N- I'm ruining my career, I'm\Ndoing it my way, understand?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:26.658,00:22:29.748,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, take a doughnut hole.\NI'm offering.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:32.208,00:22:32.538,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:33.678,00:22:37.848,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was lodged in Garrett\NDelaney's sinus cavity.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:37.848,00:22:38.868,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,.22 caliber.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:40.068,00:22:44.357,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These dimples indicate\Nthat the bullet ricocheted\Naround inside the cranium.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:46.038,00:22:47.268,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you worried\Nabout your doctorate?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:47.718,00:22:50.868,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Dr. Grayson touched me\Nwith an open hand\Non the shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:52.338,00:22:53.508,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean inappropriately?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:53.658,00:22:55.608,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I read a book\Non body language.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:55.698,00:22:59.298,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently in our culture,\Nwhen an older male lays\Nan open hand on a younger male,
Dialogue: 0,00:22:59.598,00:23:00.618,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it conveys approval.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:00.978,00:23:05.058,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if he bumps younger\Nmale with a closed fist,\Nit conveys doubt.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:05.208,00:23:09.168,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Grayson went like this,\Nnot like this.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:10.398,00:23:12.228,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like this.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:13.278,00:23:15.738,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not like this.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:16.878,00:23:20.621,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Grayson is elderly\Nand arthritic.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:20.658,00:23:23.387,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps he simply needed help\Ngetting to his feet like this.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:24.978,00:23:28.007,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Brennan,\Nvisitors in your office.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:29.236,00:23:35.838,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tempe, this is a friend\Nof Dad's.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:37.068,00:23:40.368,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father Coulter is Toby Coulter,\Ntrain trestle guy.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:41.598,00:23:43.308,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.\NI remember that story.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:43.308,00:23:46.548,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Dad and his friend\Naccidentally blew up\Na train trestle.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:46.668,00:23:48.857,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. How do you\Naccidentally blow up\Na train trestle?
Dialogue: 0,00:23:49.008,00:23:53.548,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we were hired by a farmer\Nto dynamite the ice\Noff his stock pond.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:53.548,00:23:56.148,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We get this competition\Ngoing who's gonna\Nslide the dynamite...
Dialogue: 0,00:23:56.148,00:23:57.828,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,farther across the ice\Nbefore it blows.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:58.327,00:24:00.616,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know it's a federal offense\Nto blow up a train trestle,\NFather.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:00.918,00:24:02.537,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, even if it is\Naccidental.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:02.628,00:24:05.958,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father Toby Coulter,\Nmeet my partner, Seeley Booth.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:06.378,00:24:09.015,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Careful. He's F.B.I.\N- Ooh. Well, I'm innocent.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:09.348,00:24:11.687,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Max's toss that brought\Nthe trestle down.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:11.742,00:24:14.867,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Max Keenan's best friend\Ngrows up to be a priest.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:15.048,00:24:17.328,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure your people have\Nthat fact on file somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:18.378,00:24:20.388,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tempe, Father Coulter\Nhas a message from Dad.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:21.029,00:24:22.038,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a private message.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:23.928,00:24:24.708,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to my office.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:29.541,00:24:32.598,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's just gonna\Ntell Agent Booth anyway.\NMight as well let him listen.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:35.928,00:24:38.088,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Back off."\NThat's the message.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:38.088,00:24:40.488,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said you'd understand.\N[ Booth ]\NWhere'd you see him?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:41.247,00:24:44.388,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In confession.\NWe're not Catholic.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:44.928,00:24:47.268,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the sanctity\Nof the confessional\Nis extended to all.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:48.318,00:24:50.538,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, did he ever call you\Non your cell phone, Father?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:51.558,00:24:52.128,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two days ago.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:53.178,00:24:55.397,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Can I see your phone?\N- You want to trace the call?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:55.878,00:24:56.298,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:58.639,00:25:01.878,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, uh, Max Keenan,\Nhe come to you for absolution?
Dialogue: 0,00:25:02.268,00:25:04.338,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm sure you know\Nthe requirements for confession.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:04.458,00:25:07.038,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Contrition and intent\Nnot to repeat the sin.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:07.127,00:25:10.512,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Max doesn't have either.\NAnd as a priest, I failed him.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:11.034,00:25:13.308,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never was able to get him\Nto walk the straight and narrow.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:14.178,00:25:15.288,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything else\Nyou can tell us?
Dialogue: 0,00:25:16.098,00:25:18.378,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he was angry.\NHe felt his hand\Nhad been forced.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:18.651,00:25:19.998,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where can we reach you,\NFather?
Dialogue: 0,00:25:20.328,00:25:22.518,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father Coulter's staying\Nat St. Augustine Seminary...
Dialogue: 0,00:25:22.518,00:25:24.408,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for the next few days\Nbefore heading back to Ohio.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:25.038,00:25:25.878,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, Father.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:26.988,00:25:28.818,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father loves you.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:29.841,00:25:31.607,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that part\Nof Dad's message?
Dialogue: 0,00:25:32.598,00:25:33.708,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a personal\Nobservation.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:46.518,00:25:48.408,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Booth ]\NDelaney's murder,\Nthe threats on Russ's life,
Dialogue: 0,00:25:48.408,00:25:51.048,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this is all happening now\Nbecause of a little\Nmetal dolphin...
Dialogue: 0,00:25:51.048,00:25:52.338,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we found on\Nyour mother's grave.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:53.508,00:25:57.378,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,F.B.I. field unit in Denver\Ntraced it to a local artist\Nin Mead, Colorado.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:57.552,00:25:59.358,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who identified Dad\Nas the buyer.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:59.792,00:26:02.159,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Delaney left the F.B.I.\N15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:02.178,00:26:04.518,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And somebody told him\Nabout your dad.\NAnd didn't tell you?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:04.668,00:26:06.798,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're part of the conspiracy.\NYou must be annoyed.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:06.858,00:26:09.018,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what? I am.\NAnd I don't like finding out...
Dialogue: 0,00:26:09.018,00:26:10.728,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's a dirty F.B.I. agent\Nin this building.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:13.054,00:26:17.028,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's what I think happened.\NDelaney goes to your father.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:17.118,00:26:18.738,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He asks him to hand over\Nthe evidence.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:18.918,00:26:21.558,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't do it,\Nhe kills you or Russ.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:21.828,00:26:23.297,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad calls Russ to warn him.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:24.318,00:26:26.264,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then kills Delaney.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:26.328,00:26:29.268,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guts him, burns him,\Nleaves a calling card.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:29.658,00:26:31.070,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mess with\NMax Keenan's kids.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:31.548,00:26:33.416,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I supposed to like that?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:34.636,00:26:38.208,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Bones. I'll take a stand-up\Ncrook over a crooked cop\Nany day of the week.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:38.262,00:26:41.748,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Booth, I got us a meet\Nwith the judge. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:41.808,00:26:44.388,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you better get back\Nto your lab in case\Nwe're successful.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:45.583,00:26:47.598,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just find it best\Nto do what she says.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.47,0:26:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:49.275,00:26:52.668,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to exhume\Nthe young F.B.I. agent\Nthat Marvin Beckett murdered?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:52.758,00:26:53.778,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's correct,\NYour Honor.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:54.798,00:26:57.648,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- That is a big, noisy mess\Nin the making.\N- [ Door Opens ]
Dialogue: 0,00:26:59.357,00:27:03.948,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The F.B.I. has credible evidence\Nthat the homicide case against\NMarvin Beckett was manufactured.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:04.490,00:27:07.878,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Assistant United States\NAttorney Dan Burridge arguing\Nagainst this writ, Judge Kemper.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:08.718,00:27:09.990,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- On behalf of--\N- The F.B.I.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:10.776,00:27:12.858,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I thought you were F.B.I.?\N- I am, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:13.548,00:27:16.278,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you.\NA big, noisy mess.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:16.698,00:27:18.978,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.\NLet's hear your argument,\NMr. Burridge.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:19.098,00:27:22.248,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a precipitant exhumation\Nin a highly inflammatory case.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:22.248,00:27:25.158,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The evidence to which\NMiss Julian alludes\Nhas not been authenticated.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:25.158,00:27:27.978,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has been authenticated\Nby the Jeffersonian Institution.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:28.005,00:27:30.948,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The F.B.I. would like to do\Ntheir own in-house analysis\Nbefore proceeding.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:31.068,00:27:33.948,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course they would.\NThey're the ones who did\Nthe framing 30 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:34.098,00:27:37.306,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I take exception to that.\NWhy? You weren't even\Nborn 30 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:37.338,00:27:38.928,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Judge--\N- Not like me\Nand Judge Kemper...
Dialogue: 0,00:27:38.958,00:27:41.988,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who got to see firsthand what\NMarvin Beckett was really like.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:42.408,00:27:47.087,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Julian, did you bring\Nthis to me because I knew\NMarvin Beckett personally?
Dialogue: 0,00:27:47.658,00:27:50.178,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you? I wasn't aware\Nof that, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:50.598,00:27:51.978,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you aware of that,\NAgent Booth?
Dialogue: 0,00:27:53.118,00:27:56.777,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like to do this slowly\Nand carefully, Judge.\NThat's all.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:56.898,00:27:59.748,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we want to exhume Gus Harper\Nso we can make sure...
Dialogue: 0,00:27:59.748,00:28:02.719,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was murdered in exactly\Nthe way the damn F.B.I....
Dialogue: 0,00:28:02.748,00:28:04.693,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,said he was murdered,\NYour Honor.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:05.838,00:28:10.308,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Saroyan ] As mandated\Nby the writ of exhumation\Nby Judge Theodore Kemper...
Dialogue: 0,00:28:10.308,00:28:12.527,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the D.C. Federal\NJudicial District,
Dialogue: 0,00:28:12.678,00:28:16.098,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, Dr. Camille Saroyan,\Nwill be performing an autopsy...
Dialogue: 0,00:28:16.098,00:28:18.587,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of Special Agent\NAugustus Donald Harper...
Dialogue: 0,00:28:18.918,00:28:21.346,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,under the auspices of\Nthe Jeffersonian Institution.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:21.618,00:28:25.097,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Date of death:\NJune 25, 1978.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:25.338,00:28:28.698,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Date of internment:\NJuly 2, 1978.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:28.968,00:28:31.185,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Date of exhumation:\Nthat would be today.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:31.398,00:28:35.027,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also present\Nat the post-exhumation autopsy\Nis Dr. Temperance Brennan.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:35.353,00:28:39.138,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The original autopsy in 1978\Nfound that Agent Harper...
Dialogue: 0,00:28:39.168,00:28:42.228,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was killed when he was shot\Nthree times at close range...
Dialogue: 0,00:28:42.498,00:28:45.227,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by a .38 Colt Detective\NSpecial revolver.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:45.529,00:28:48.348,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two shots to the chest,\None piercing the heart.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:48.676,00:28:49.848,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other, the left lung.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:50.178,00:28:53.388,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The third, a shot\Nto the frontal bone.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:57.528,00:29:00.828,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What?\N- That bullet hole in the head,\Nthat's from a .38.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:00.918,00:29:04.038,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Just like the coroner said.\N- I can already tell\Nthese two holes...
Dialogue: 0,00:29:04.728,00:29:07.137,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are from something\Na whole lot bigger than\Na snub-nosed revolver.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:07.578,00:29:10.398,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something more like a rifle\Nthat a sniper would use.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:10.521,00:29:14.418,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Zack, you'd better get\Na full set of X-rays\Nbefore Dr. Saroyan reopens.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:15.288,00:29:17.418,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna conduct this one\Nlike the whole world\Nis watching.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:18.629,00:29:27.166,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Russ.\NOkay, I'm here.\NWhat's up?
Dialogue: 0,00:29:28.187,00:29:28.788,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know,\Nyou're an idiot, Russ.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:29.358,00:29:31.728,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like you,\Nbut you're a real idiot.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:32.508,00:29:35.328,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd I do?\NI got a call from\Nyour parole officer today.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:35.93,00:29:37.010,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,00:29:37.638,00:29:39.405,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Because you crossed\Nstate lines without\Ninforming him.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:40.547,00:29:42.117,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just told him you were aiding\Nin an F.B.I. investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.85,0:29:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:47.088,00:29:47.868,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're slipping,\Naren't ya?
Dialogue: 0,00:29:49.158,00:29:50.658,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I want to marry Amy\Nand raise her kids.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:50.958,00:29:53.027,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of them is sick.\NThat costs money.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:53.504,00:29:56.687,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a felon on parole.\NI work part-time as a mechanic.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:56.688,00:30:00.768,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You tell me what job am I gonna\Nget that lets me be the man\NI need to be to raise a family?
Dialogue: 0,00:30:00.858,00:30:03.632,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got this sick little girl\Ndepending on you. I get that.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:05.448,00:30:08.527,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you go back inside\Nand you cross that line,\Nyou're not helping anyone out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.84,0:30:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Gunshot ]\N[ Woman Screams ]
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.31,0:30:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody down!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.38,0:30:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ People Shouting,\NGasping ]
Dialogue: 0,00:30:39.163,00:30:40.807,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Melissa ]\NYou hear about cancer.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:41.444,00:30:43.632,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just was afraid\Nthat I would lose my son.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:44.959,00:30:46.423,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think, why us?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.68,00:30:48.973,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, why me?\NWhy my child?
Dialogue: 0,00:30:50.563,00:30:52.813,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Marlo Thomas ] You can\Njoin the battle to save lives
Dialogue: 0,00:30:53.833,00:30:56.593,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by supporting St. Jude\NChildren's Research Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:57.613,00:31:02.053,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is such a gift to give hope\Nback to a family.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:02.443,00:31:04.362,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a dad,\NI'm eternally grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.90,0:31:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Non-English speech ]
Dialogue: 0,00:31:10.573,00:31:13.063,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Marlo Thomas ] Join St. Jude\Nwith your debit or credit card
Dialogue: 0,00:31:13.094,00:31:14.623,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for only $19 a month,
Dialogue: 0,00:31:14.923,00:31:17.383,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and we'll send you\Nthis St. Jude T-shirt.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:18.853,00:31:21.043,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,St. Jude is only possible
Dialogue: 0,00:31:21.043,00:31:22.993,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because of the people\Nwho donate.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:23.415,00:31:25.243,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're saving children's lives.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:25.397,00:31:27.193,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're keeping families together
Dialogue: 0,00:31:27.373,00:31:29.293,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,during the hardest thing\Nthey've ever faced.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:30.373,00:31:33.193,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Marlo Thomas ] Please call\Nor go online right now
Dialogue: 0,00:31:33.643,00:31:35.443,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and become\Na St. Jude partner in hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.19,0:32:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[school bells]
Dialogue: 0,00:32:08.743,00:32:12.823,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When pain says, “I'm here,”
Dialogue: 0,00:32:13.933,00:32:17.473,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I say, “So are they.”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.64,0:32:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,00:32:21.251,00:32:21.582,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ALEVE
Dialogue: 0,00:32:22.153,00:32:23.293,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Who do you take it\Nfor?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.74,0:33:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,00:33:28.873,00:33:31.033,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not leaving\Nwithout these diamonds!
Dialogue: 0,00:33:31.123,00:33:31.693,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Diamonds?
Dialogue: 0,00:33:32.083,00:33:33.223,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just here for the stains.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:33.433,00:33:34.783,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With Persil ProClean.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.31,0:33:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,BOOM.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:36.431,00:33:37.180,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's more than Clean.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:37.183,00:33:38.555,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Persil ProClean.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:09.493,00:35:12.643,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Woman On TV ] Civil rights\Nactivist and convicted\Nmurderer Marvin Beckett...
Dialogue: 0,00:35:12.673,00:35:15.133,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was released today\Nwhen a second autopsy...
Dialogue: 0,00:35:15.133,00:35:17.923,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on his alleged victim,\NF.B.I. Agent Gus Harper,
Dialogue: 0,00:35:18.133,00:35:22.693,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,revealed inconsistencies\Nwith details of Mr. Beckett's\Ntrial back in 1979.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:23.293,00:35:24.673,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Coulter ]\NWhat kind\Nof inconsistencies?
Dialogue: 0,00:35:25.362,00:35:28.033,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have your confidences\Nto keep, Father.\NI have mine.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:28.578,00:35:29.563,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's over, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:35:29.564,00:35:33.163,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, now that it's out,\Nthere's no reason to kill Russ.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:33.522,00:35:35.533,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the men behind this,\Nthey don't care\Nabout Marvin Beckett.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:35.563,00:35:38.593,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They care\Nabout being exposed.\NLucky you were together.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:39.012,00:35:42.193,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why were you together?\NOh, you know,\Na man's gotta eat.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:43.411,00:35:47.563,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that some people\Nstill refuse to believe\Nin guardian angels.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:48.133,00:35:48.493,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Booth!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.39,00:35:54.253,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?\N[ Booth ]\NDeputy Director Kirby.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:54.373,00:35:55.633,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My boss's boss's boss.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:00.550,00:36:03.883,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're what's known as a real\Npain in the ass, Agent Booth.\NYes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:05.713,00:36:07.333,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just had my testicles\Nhanded to me...
Dialogue: 0,00:36:07.333,00:36:10.003,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by the attorney general of\Nthe United States of America.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:11.773,00:36:14.473,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted to know why\Nthis Marvin Beckett issue...
Dialogue: 0,00:36:14.473,00:36:17.953,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wasn't done slowly\Nand carefully with\Ngreater forethought and tact.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:17.953,00:36:19.033,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what\NI told him?\NNo, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:19.093,00:36:20.893,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told him I did not know.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:21.523,00:36:23.623,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, I had to do it the way\NI did it because the F.B.I.--
Dialogue: 0,00:36:23.676,00:36:25.573,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not your decision, Booth.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:26.422,00:36:29.533,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're suspended without pay.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:31.723,00:36:33.373,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gun, I.D.,\Nsecurity card, please.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:33.763,00:36:35.983,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, I'm entitled\Nto the reading\Nof the charges against me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.43,0:36:39.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The charges against you...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.20,0:36:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are that I was pissed upon\Nfrom a very great height!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.27,0:36:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're out of here\Nin 10 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.51,0:36:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can they do that?\NJust kick you out\Nwithout any warning?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.25,0:36:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The two guys standing\Nbehind me with the guns\Nseemed to think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.28,0:36:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, Harper's\Nribs and sternum were\Npractically obliterated...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.72,0:37:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by the two shots\Nto his torso.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.65,0:37:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Zack, Booth got fired.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.86,0:37:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Suspended, not fired.\N- Suspended's F.B.I.-speak\Nfor fired.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.76,0:37:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what hurts\Nthe most? They took the car.\NI got no wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.66,0:37:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bullets themselves\Nwere removed from the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.23,0:37:15.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- But Hodgins found some\Nvery small fragments.\N- Copper, lead, polymer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.84,0:37:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, this is\Na conspiracy, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.21,0:37:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guys, what we're dealing with\Nhere is that Booth won't be\Nworking with us anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.01,0:37:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I got my own gun.\NIt's just, God, why did they\Nhave to take the company car?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.31,0:37:28.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume that the only way\NBooth can get his car back...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.38,0:37:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would be to solve\Nthe case on his own\Nand that we'd help.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.78,0:37:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. No, no.\NI can't let you guys do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.25,0:37:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who wants to help Booth,\Nraise their hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.53,0:37:46.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I reverse engineered\Nto find the most likely design\Nof the bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.17,0:37:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After the bullet spread,\Nlead pellets were released\Nlike buckshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.97,0:37:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second.\NThat's a homemade round\Ninvented back in the '70s.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.14,0:37:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We're talking a military-issue\NM-40 A-1 sniper rifle.\N- Nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.61,0:38:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dude, what you call being\Na conspiracy theorist,\NI call being well-informed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.08,0:38:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.\NGus Harper was murdered\Nby a military sniper?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.25,0:38:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Who makes his own rounds.\N- Maybe we could compare it to\Nthe bullet that grazed Russ.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.19,0:38:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a civilian.\NWe don't have access\Nto that round.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.29,0:38:13.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Caroline can help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.86,0:38:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Booth ]\NYou still have a job?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.83,0:38:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not for long.\NI'm on performance review.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.63,0:38:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None of the F.B.I. members\Nof the Bank Robbery Task Force\Nhad sniper training in the '70s.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.57,0:38:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to know who else\Nwas on that task force.\NLocal--
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.97,0:38:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Booth! Booth!\NI got it figured out.\NState cops, A.T.F.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.31,0:38:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if any of 'em had sniper\Ntraining. Once you find out,\Nyou keep your head down.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.48,0:38:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Task force, sniper training,\N'70s, duck. Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.25,0:38:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured out a way to solve\Nthe case and get your job back.\NWow. That'd be great.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.02,0:38:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need my father to give us the\Nrest of the evidence he stole\Nfrom that safety-deposit box.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.69,0:38:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great.\NI'll drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.29,0:38:49.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Saroyan,\Nwhen I get my doctorate,\NI'd like to work here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.67,0:38:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Zack, you are\Nan excellent scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.13,0:38:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But an important part\Nof the job is appearing\Nas an expert witness in court.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.60,0:38:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Ooh.\N- "Ooh," what?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.01,0:39:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jurors have to take you\Nseriously. And frankly,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.64,0:39:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you look like a weekend fill-in\Nat a college radio station.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.58,0:39:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Truth hurts, dude.\NLearn from it and grow.\N[ Chuckles ]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.56,0:39:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't able to find Max\Nby tracing him through the\Ncell phone call he made to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.59,0:39:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Call came over\Nthe Internet.\NIt was untraceable.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.90,0:39:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Max always\Ndid things his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.33,0:39:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess your being\Na priest didn't have much\Nof an affect on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.03,0:39:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Son, I spent my whole life\Ntrying to turn Max's life\Nto Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.34,0:39:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He knows exactly\None Bible verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.61,0:39:37.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers 35:19.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.08,0:39:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The revenger of blood himself\Nshall slay the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.08,0:39:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When he meeteth him,\Nhe shall slay him."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.68,0:39:47.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that mean?\NThat's the law\Nof the jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.62,0:39:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father Coulter, if my father\Nmakes contact with you again,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.76,0:39:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,please tell him\Nhe needs to trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.16,0:39:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His way got my mother murdered\Nand almost got Russ killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.06,0:39:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- It's time he tried my way.\N- He won't contact me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.90,0:40:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Well, how do you know?\N- Ask him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.07,0:40:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He put me under surveillance.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.04,0:40:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If a parish priest\Ncan figure out the F.B.I.\Nis watching him,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.61,0:40:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so can an experienced\Nfugitive like your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.29,0:40:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need a makeover.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.60,0:40:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Sighs ]\NZack, I am a big believer\Nin people being themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.30,0:40:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're actually\Nkind of cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.67,0:40:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I've been told that\Nmany times.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.91,0:40:41.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Usually followed\Nby the word "but."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.17,0:40:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this case, "But no one\Ntakes you seriously."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.41,0:40:47.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need help, Angela.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.72,0:40:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do I do first?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.80,0:41:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lose the floppy hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.80,0:41:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Groans ]
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.24,0:41:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you mad at me?\N[ Sighs ]\NI need a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.57,0:41:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you don't.\NYou got me. I'm your gun.\NYou want equipment?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.17,0:41:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here. Have these. All right?\NNew division of labor.\NI shoot 'em, you cuff 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.45,0:41:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell me\Nyou had Father Coulter\Nunder surveillance?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.95,0:41:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is my job to find your dad\Nand put him in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.42,0:41:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you don't think\NI'll help.\NHe's your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.02,0:41:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't think I should\Nhave to ask you to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.22,0:41:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He abandoned me, Booth.\NAnd that's the best thing\Nyou can say about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.73,0:41:33.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father lives\Nby a certain code.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.63,0:41:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And part of that code\Nis defending his family\Nby whatever means necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.10,0:41:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean killing people\Nand setting their corpses\Non fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.67,0:41:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- "Any means necessary"\Nsort of covers that.\N- You respect him?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.47,0:41:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just saying in his world,\Nhe's a very honorable man.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.40,0:41:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous.\NThere's only one world.\NIt's this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.27,0:41:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would that be the one world\Nwhere you're mad at me for\Ntrying to catch your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.48,0:41:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or the other world where you\Nactually want him caught?\NNeither.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.71,0:41:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to pick one.\NEither. Both.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.18,0:41:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Brennan, Agent Booth,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.92,0:42:01.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you'd like to meet\Nthe reason we're all losing\Nour jobs and getting shot at.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.42,0:42:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is\NMr. Marvin Beckett.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.22,0:42:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I wanted\Nto thank you personally.\N- You're welcome, Mr. Beckett.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.09,0:42:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thirty years ago,\Ncrooked agents put me in jail\Nfor something I did not do.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.83,0:42:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did not kill\Nthe young F.B.I. agent.\NI did not steal the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.94,0:42:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I thank you for proving it\Nto the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.90,0:42:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm here to tell you\Nto your face, to assure you,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.41,0:42:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did not do those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.41,0:42:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You freed an innocent man.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.38,0:42:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And in return,\NI must warn you,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.58,0:42:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the people that did this\Nto me aren't just a bunch\Nof corrupt cops.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.95,0:42:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They serve masters\Nof much greater influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.59,0:42:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're looking to bring their\Nworld down around their ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.79,0:42:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They will strike at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.76,0:42:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.07,0:42:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's your list of snipers\Nfrom the decade of disco.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.27,0:42:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This time I'm advising you.\NDuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.11,0:42:58.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone you know?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.85,0:43:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The A.T.F. rep on the task force\Nwas a marine sniper,\NRobert Kirby.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.92,0:43:05.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,F.B.I. Deputy Director\NRobert Kirby?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.29,0:43:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That just suspended you?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.39,0:43:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Call your brother, tell him\Nto get out of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.56,0:43:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell him to get out now.\NWhy? What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.53,0:43:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seconds after Caroline\Ngot this list,\NKirby knew about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.06,0:43:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not answering.\NI don't understand, Booth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.17,0:43:22.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not us that Kirby\Nis afraid of.\NIt's your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.17,0:43:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only way to strike at him\Nis to go through you or Russ.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.14,0:43:28.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kirby was the one that\Ntook a shot at Russ.\NNo answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.91,0:43:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Russ?\NHello?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.71,0:43:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- All right, just stay back.\N- Russ?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.18,0:43:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- There's no sign of a break-in.\NI'll check the back. Russ?\N-  Russ?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.79,0:43:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.92,0:43:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Booth?\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.19,0:43:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Russ.\NJust take it easy, all right?\NWe don't know that for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.50,0:43:54.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's too much blood.\NNobody could survive that--\Nthat much blood loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.33,0:43:56.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.97,0:44:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Okay.\NIt's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.04,0:44:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.91,0:44:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.82,0:44:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not leaving\Nwithout these diamonds!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.99,0:44:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Diamonds?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.99,0:44:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just here for the stains.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.42,0:44:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With Persil ProClean.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.49,0:44:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,BOOM.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.33,0:44:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's more than Clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.33,0:44:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Persil ProClean.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.07,0:45:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does it fee like
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.04,0:45:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To sell your car to Carvana
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.07,0:45:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It feels amazing, you get a\Ngreat offer in seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.25,0:45:47.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That feels too good to be true
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.31,0:45:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With kicking back and relaxing
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.25,0:45:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As we pick up your car
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.55,0:45:54.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when you get paid\Non the spot
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.05,0:45:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It feels like scoring big
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.19,0:45:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know the feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.29,0:45:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just never imagined
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.19,0:46:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could get it\Nfrom selling your car
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.36,0:46:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, with Carvana
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.96,0:46:06.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can experience the new way\Nto sell a car
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.50,0:46:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[school bells]
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.90,0:46:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When pain says, “I'm here,”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.61,0:46:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I say, “So are they.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.94,0:46:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪♪
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.95,0:46:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ALEVE
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.18,0:46:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Who do you take it\Nfor?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.89,0:48:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's against the law\Nus not calling in a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.69,0:48:43.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a murder.\NIt was a bloodstain.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.72,0:48:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That much blood,\Nit's mur-- it's murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.79,0:48:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We call it in, the next thing\Nis we find ourselves\Nunder arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.90,0:48:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That had to be Russ's blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.77,0:48:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got a sample, right?\NWe'll check the D.N.A.\Nat the lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.14,0:49:02.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until then, who's the one\Nwho always says, "Don't jump\Nto conclusions"? Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.78,0:49:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.21,0:49:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.92,0:49:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish you wouldn't keep letting\Nme hug you when I get scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.85,0:49:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, when I get scared,\NI'll hug you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.19,0:49:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll call it even.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.19,0:49:23.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Results?\NThe blood's not Russ's.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.60,0:49:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even you can't do\Na D.N.A. test that fast.\NDidn't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.10,0:49:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both Brennan and her brother\Nare "O" type blood,\Nas was the mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.54,0:49:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The blood sample\Nyou brought me was "AB."
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.21,0:49:34.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore--\NOkay, let's go tell Bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.34,0:49:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just saw her.\NShe's on her way\Nto see the priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.64,0:49:38.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?\NHe said he had\Nsomething for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.64,0:49:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She can't be going places\Nwithout me. Not when it's\Nopen season on Brennans.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.61,0:49:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Cell Phone Rings ]\NBones?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.18,0:49:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Caroline ]\NNot even close,\Nchéri.\NWe need to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.32,0:49:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, first, I want to tell you\Nthat your brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.19,0:49:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is, uh, with his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.09,0:49:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean... with God?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.20,0:50:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, his earthly father--\Nyour father.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.17,0:50:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you certain?\NSaw it with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.74,0:50:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thank God.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.64,0:50:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which I use only\Nas a figure of speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.94,0:50:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you have\Nto start somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.21,0:50:16.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, you're--\Nyou're very much like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.75,0:50:19.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm-- I'm nothing\Nlike my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.59,0:50:22.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black and white.\NThe two of you, you always saw\Nthe world in black and white.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.32,0:50:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mother wasn't like that.\NEither is Russell.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.80,0:50:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, go.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.73,0:50:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was clearing out my desk\Nwhen my phone rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.57,0:50:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's this F.B.I.\Nagent named Carlson.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.51,0:50:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He heads up\Na surveillance unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.97,0:50:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He tells me you and Booth\Nare wasting my time\Nwith this damn priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.58,0:50:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tell him, "You better mind\Nyour mushy mouth."
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.51,0:50:47.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gotta find Bones,\Nkeep her from getting killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.98,0:50:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father Coulter\Nis 90 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.55,0:50:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,confined to bed with Alzheimer's\Nin a convalescent home\Nout there at the seminary.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.55,0:50:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which does not much sound like\Nthe priest you told me about.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.32,0:51:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father,\Nhe talked about, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.06,0:51:04.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when you were four\Nand your brother was nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.96,0:51:07.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And-- And he hid\Nbehind this door and\Nhe jumped out at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.43,0:51:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You know what? Just give me\Nthe keys to your car.\N- My car?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.17,0:51:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boo! He hollers, "Boo!"\NAnd you-- you had this doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.11,0:51:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Had this string in the back\Nfor talking.\NChatty Cathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.45,0:51:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wham!\NYou took that doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.08,0:51:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you wound up. And you hit\Nyour brother so hard you knocked\Nhim flat as a pancake.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.02,0:51:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said to your mother,\N"No one will ever jump out\Nat that girl again."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.59,0:51:33.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And your mother said,\N"Just like you, Max.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.63,0:51:35.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's just like you."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.63,0:51:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hair color, plastic surgery,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.24,0:51:46.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,colored contact lenses,\Nchin and cheek implants,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.01,0:51:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,15 years older.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.28,0:51:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still,\NI should have seen it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.05,0:52:01.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Tires Screech ]\N[ Horn Honks ]
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.56,0:52:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Line Ringing ]\NCome on, Bones.\NPick up. Pick up!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.73,0:52:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Dr. Temperance Brennan.\NLeave a message.\NDamn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.16,0:52:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Russ knew it was you\Nall along?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.63,0:52:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.44,0:52:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You talk to Russ,\Nbut not to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.48,0:52:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know,\Nto tell you the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.41,0:52:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you do better without me\Nand Russ does worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.05,0:52:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this.\NI'm not religious.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.75,0:52:36.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. We're gonna play\Nthis your way. Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.99,0:52:42.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Gus Harper's journal.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.86,0:52:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a key there that's\Nto a safety-deposit box.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.36,0:52:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that safety-deposit box\Nis all the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.50,0:52:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you give it\Nto them back in 1978?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.51,0:52:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because your mother took\None look at it and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.81,0:52:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If you turn this over to them,\Nthey will kill us\Nand our kids."
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.21,0:53:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They got Mom anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.55,0:53:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's not a day that goes by\Nthat my heart is not broken.\N[ Vehicle Approaching ]
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.06,0:53:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.19,0:53:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gotta go.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.47,0:53:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.\NI can't let you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.67,0:53:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I love you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.80,0:53:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I mean,\NI can't let you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.44,0:53:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'm sorry.\N- [ Moans ]
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.48,0:53:35.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must be getting old.\NI let you get the drop on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.75,0:53:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I'm sorry.\NI just can't let you get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.19,0:53:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.\NListen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.06,0:53:50.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you find somebody that you\Ncan trust, you hang on to him.\NRemember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.63,0:53:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, let's go!\NI'm proud of you.\NI love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.47,0:53:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.18,0:54:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You take care of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.15,0:54:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- F.B.I. Stop or I'll shoot.\N- Booth.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.19,0:54:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Booth. Booth.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.81,0:54:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.55,0:54:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Did he really\Nhave to hit the car?\NI wasn't gonna chase him.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.10,0:55:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.60,0:55:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪♪ [ Indie Rock ]
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.68,0:55:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[ Man ]\N♪ And if I only could
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.48,0:55:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ I'd make a deal with God
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.68,0:55:22.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ And I'd get him\Nto swap our places ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.72,0:55:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Be running up that road
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.26,0:55:27.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Be running up that hill
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.73,0:55:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Be running up that building
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.33,0:55:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ If I only could
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.31,0:55:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ You don't wanna hurt me
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.38,0:55:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ But see how deep\Nthe bullet lies ♪
